</ol>

GREED
<li> How many credit cards do you own? <br>
Out of the four or five that I have, I only use two. 
<li> What's your guilty pleasure? <br>
I would say poker, but I don't really feel guilty about that.  Pornography, perhaps, but I lost that shame a while ago, so I would have to pin it on an overwhelming desire to own more consumer electronics than I really have need for. 
<li> If you had $1 million, what would you do with it? <br>
Invest most of it, and play in a few poker tournaments. 
<li> Would you rather be rich or famous? <br>
Rich.  Both are fleeting, but I'd rather be secure with the future and my family. 
<li> Would you accept a boring job if it meant you would make megabucks? <br>
Yes. 
<li> Have you ever stolen anything? <br>
Yes, if you count mp3s, pirated software/media, the unaired <i>Buffy</i> episodes "Earshot" and "Graduation Day II" during the summer between seasons 3 and 4, and a mixed variety of jelly beans, M&amp;Ms, and Brach candies from supermarkets. 
<li> How many mp3's are on your hard drive? <br>
Around 1500. 
</ol>

